				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">If you can use ram to store levels, use LZ77 (history compression) or LZ78 (dictionary compression).  If it's good enough for Zelda Oracle of Ages, it's good enough for you.
<br />LZ78 is better if you're more memory constrained.
<br />Of course, this completely depends on what your levels look like.  If there are frequently appearing sequences of tiles across multiple maps, LZ78 is the one to pick.</div>

					
