					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">never-obsolete wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I figured I'd toss my hat into the ring. <a href="http://never-obsolete.110mb.com/nesdev/files/MapEd.zip" class="postlink">MapEd</a>. The editor spits out raw files that are ready to be incbin'ed into a source.<br /><br />Metatiles are 4x4 tiles, screens are 8x8 metatiles. Maps max out at 8x8 screens.<br /><br />There is a basic tile attribute (not palette attribute) editor that allows you to assign a value ($0-$F) to a 2x2 subtile. Its up to the game engine to interpret what it means. In the picture, they are used as movement penalties.<br /><br />(Pics of a seriously useful utility)<br /></div>
<br />
<br />Great job on the Map editor, Never-Obsolete!
<br />
<br />Though there is one of the things that I need before I use this: Support for 2x2 tiles (16x16 pixel metatiles), I would really appreciate it if that was the default metatile size!</div>

